    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    ActiveActor
    Represents an active game actor with an image, position, and movement capabilities.
    ActiveActorDestructible
    Represents an actor that can be destroyed within the game.
    Boss
    Represents a boss in the game, extending the FighterPlane class.
    BossProjectile
    Represents a projectile fired by the boss plane in the game.
    Controller
    The Controller class manages the flow of the game, specifically the navigation between levels.
    Destructible
    Represents an entity that can take damage and be destroyed within the game.
    EnemyPlane
    Represents an enemy plane in the game.
    EnemyProjectile
    Represents a projectile fired by an enemy plane in the game.
    FighterPlane
    Represents a generic fighter plane in the game.
    GameOverImage
    Represents the "Game Over" image displayed when the game ends.
    HeartDisplay
    Represents a heart display to visually show the player's health as hearts.
    LevelFour
    Represents the fourth level of the game, combining standard enemies with a boss fight.
    LevelOne
    Represents the first level of the game.
    LevelParent
    Represents a level in the game, acting as the parent class for specific level implementations.
    LevelThree
    Represents the third level of the game.
    LevelTwo
    Represents the second level in the game, LevelTwo.
    LevelView
    Handles the visual representation of the game state, including the player's heart display, win screen, and game-over screen.
    LevelViewLevelTwo
    Represents the view for Level Two of the game, displaying hearts and the shield image.
    Main
    The Main class is the entry point for launching the JavaFX application.
    MainMenuController
    Controller for the main menu of the game.
    MiniMenu
    Represents a mini in-game menu with options to continue the game or return to the main menu.
    Projectile
    Represents a base class for projectiles in the game.
    ScreenManager
    The ScreenManager class is responsible for managing the application's screens and handling transitions between different scenes.
    ShieldImage
    The ShieldImage class represents a shield image in the game.
    Tutorial
    The Tutorial class represents a tutorial screen in the application.
    UserPlane
    Represents the user-controlled plane in the game, extending the FighterPlane class.
    UserProjectile
    Represents a projectile fired by the user-controlled plane in the game.
    WinImage
    The WinImage class represents the "You Win" image displayed when the player completes the game successfully.
